    <h1> How to became a  Lawyer after completing your class 10th</h1>
    <p>
        In most countries, including India, becoming a lawyer requires completing a Bachelor of Laws (LLB) degree, which usually takes three years to complete after completing a Bachelor's degree. Therefore, it is not possible to become a lawyer after class 10th, which is usually considered a secondary school level education
    </p>
