                <p>
                    To become a lawyer, you will first need to complete your higher secondary education (class 12th) and obtain a Bachelor's degree in any field from a recognized university. Then, you can apply for admission to a law school or a university that offers a Bachelor of Laws (LLB) program.

                </p>
